DOC.brief_summary: The purpose of this study is to assess the effectiveness and safety of transcervical foley catheter as compared to prostaglandins for preinduction cervical ripening and labor induction in term nulliparous women with unfavorable cervix.
DOC.brief_title: A Comparison of Transcervical Foley Catheter and Prostaglandins for Induction of Labor at Term
DOC.criteria: singleton pregnancy nulliparous women gestational age >= 37.0 weeks Bishop score <= 5 intact amniotic membrane abscence of labor live fetus with vertex presentation no previous uterine surgical procedure major congenital anomaly
DOC.keyword: labor induction, transcervical foley catheter, prostaglandin
